{
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "artifact_type": "rig.critic.plan_review.v1",
  "plan_under_review": "fix-concurrent-session-regressions",
  "plan_revision": 1,
  "reviewer": "critic",
  "reviewed_at": "2026-05-30T00:30:00Z",
  "verdict": "APPROVE WITH CONDITIONS",
  "axis_scores": [
    {
      "axis": "Coupling",
      "score": 4,
      "finding": "pass",
      "note": "4 packets across 3 packages (desktop, opencode, app), zero cross-packet dependencies. Each packet only touches its own package. Packet A's dependency on BusEvent from ../../../bus/bus-event is pre-existing and not new coupling. No new imports appear across package boundaries."
    },
    {
      "axis": "Debuggability",
      "score": 4,
      "finding": "pass",
      "note": "All 4 packets produce compile-time errors when broken (TS2307, TS2339, TS2741), caught immediately by bun typecheck. Packet C's installCli stub is the weakest link: execFile rejection propagates raw with no error context downing the IPC handler. See Comment 3 — error wrapping recommended.",
      "recommendation": "Wrap execFileAsync call in installCli with try/catch that includes the IPC handler name in the error message."
    },
    {
      "axis": "Convergence",
      "score": 3,
      "finding": "concern",
      "note": "DuckDB test claim over-reaches — no pre-flight evidence captured. Packet B pseudocode doesn't match actual settings.tsx pattern (uses settings.general vs store.general?, update() vs setStore()). Packet A is a best-guess recreation but adequately scope-limited by dead-code mitigation.",
      "recommendation": "Capture duckdb-query.test.ts error state BEFORE and AFTER Packet A. Correct Packet B code to match inline provider pattern."
    },
    {
      "axis": "Surface area",
      "score": 5,
      "finding": "pass",
      "note": "4 files total (2 new, 2 modified). No public API surface changes, no signature changes to exported functions, no new exports added solely for testing."
    },
    {
      "axis": "Testability",
      "score": 4,
      "finding": "pass",
      "note": "Each packet independently testable via bun typecheck in its package. DuckDB test dependency on Packet A acknowledged. Packet A cannot be runtime-tested (dead code), but compile-time verification is sufficient for the regression fix.",
      "recommendation": "Explicitly run bun typecheck after each packet to verify independent convergence."
    },
    {
      "axis": "Error clarity",
      "score": 3,
      "finding": "concern",
      "note": "Compile-time errors are clear. Packet C lacks error wrapping — raw ENOENT propagates to renderer. No structured logging identifies the IPC path 'install-cli' when the handler fails.",
      "recommendation": "Add try/catch with informative re-throw or structured log.warn in installCli stub."
    },
    {
      "axis": "Reversibility",
      "score": 5,
      "finding": "pass",
      "note": "Each packet independently revertible. No cross-packet revert dependencies. Rollback plan documents exact revert order. Partial revert leaves each respective package in its original broken state (TS error)."
    }
  ],
  "comments_appended": [
    {
      "category": "boundary",
      "severity": "blocking",
      "summary": "Packet B pseudocode doesn't match actual settings.tsx provider pattern"
    },
    {
      "category": "evidence",
      "severity": "weak",
      "summary": "DuckDB test claim over-reaches without pre-flight evidence"
    },
    {
      "category": "production",
      "severity": "weak",
      "summary": "Packet C installCli stub lacks error wrapping"
    },
    {
      "category": "evidence",
      "severity": "informational",
      "summary": "Packet A event shapes should document evidence source"
    }
  ],
  "conditions_for_approval": [
    "1. (BLOCKING) Packet B: Replace the pseudocode showing standalone `const showSessionViz = () => ...` and `update()` calls with the exact inline pattern matching the existing 14 entries: `showSessionViz: withFallback(() => store.general?.showSessionViz, false)` and `setShowSessionViz(value: boolean) { setStore(\"general\", \"showSessionViz\", value) }`. The current pseudocode will mislead literal executors.",
    "2. (WEAK) Packet C: Add error wrapping to the `installCli` stub. At minimum wrap the `execFileAsync` call in try/catch with `new Error(\`installCli: failed to exec opencode --version: ${err.message}\`)` so IPC handler failures are traceable.",
    "3. (WEAK) Claim atom 6: Capture duckdb-query.test.ts failure output BEFORE applying Packet A. After Packet A, run again and report both outputs as evidence. If the pre-fix error is not solely TuiEvent-related, update the claim."
  ],
  "follow_up_issues": [
    "1. Packet A's TuiEvent module is dead code — no consumer subscribes to these bus events after the TUI was deleted. File a follow-up to remove the TuiEvent publish calls from mcp/index.ts and handlers/tui.ts, and delete the recreated module. The HTTP API routes referencing TuiEvent (groups/tui.ts) should also be marked for deprecation.",
    "2. The 36 dirty files reported by cartography indicate active parallel sessions. If the install-cli.ts file or settings.tsx changes conflict with parallel work, the build will break again. Document the conflict strategy for these files."
  ]
}
